Residential Structure Fire Smoke Detector Analysis

Nakai Zemer - Fire Planning Division

2023-01-05

#importing datasets
imagetrend_incidents_raw_df <-
  fread('./Datasets/incidents.csv', na.strings = "NULL")

#creating residential structure fire dataset from imagetrend data
residential_fires_df <- imagetrend_incidents_raw_df %>%
  filter(
    property_use_code == "419",
    incident_type_code %in% c("111", "121"),
    report_completed_flag == 1,
    between(incident_date, "2018-01-01", "2022-12-31")
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    id = paste0(incident_number, "-", exposure_number),
    incident_date_time = incident_date,
    incident_date = as.Date(incident_date)
  ) %>%
  relocate(id)

Data Source

All data was sourced from ImageTrend between 1/1/2018-12/31/2022.

Definitions

Residential structure fires are defined as an incident type 111 (Building fire) or 112 (Fires in structure other than in a building) occurring at a location with a property use code of 419 (1 or 2 family dwelling). Exposures in this analysis are included in all figures if the exposure meets the criteria as a residential structure. Station territories are associated to calls based on which territory they occurred inside.

structure_fire_count_by_year_df <- residential_fires_df %>%
  group_by(year = year(incident_date), incident_type_code) %>%
  summarize(count = n())

structure_fire_freq_tab_df <-
  data.frame(freq(year(residential_fires_df$incident_date)))

detectors_df <- residential_fires_df %>%
  group_by(
           presence_of_detectors,
           detector_effectiveness) %>%
  summarize(count = n())

#Spatial Joins

station_territories_shp <-
  st_read(
    "C:/Users/ZemerN036438/OneDrive - Kennesaw State University/Data Science/ESRI/Shapefiles/Shapefiles/StationTerritories.shp",
    quiet = TRUE
  )


residential_fires_shp <- residential_fires_df %>%
  #filter(latitude != 0) %>%
  st_as_sf(
    coords = c("longitude", "latitude"),
    agr = "constant",
    crs = "WGS84",
    remove = FALSE
  )

residential_fires_shp <-
  st_transform(residential_fires_shp, st_crs(station_territories_shp))

spacial_join <-
  st_join(residential_fires_shp, station_territories_shp, join = st_within) %>% filter(!is.na(Station))

residential_fires_stations_df <- as.data.frame(spacial_join)

map_palette <- "OrRd"

structure_fires_by_station <- spacial_join %>%
  group_by(NAME) %>%
  summarize(Count = n())
  
structure_fires_by_station <- st_join(station_territories_shp, structure_fires_by_station)

detectors_by_station <- spacial_join %>%
  filter(presence_of_detectors %in% c("Present", "None present")) %>%
  group_by(NAME, presence_of_detectors) %>%
  summarize(Count = n()) %>%
  group_by(NAME) %>%
  mutate(ratio = Count / sum(Count))

detectors_by_station <- st_join(station_territories_shp, detectors_by_station)

detectors_present_ratio <- detectors_by_station %>%
  group_by(NAME.x) %>%
  mutate(present_ratio = case_when(presence_of_detectors == "Present" ~ ratio,
                                   TRUE ~ 1 - ratio),
         present_ratio = case_when(present_ratio < 0.5 ~ 0.5,
                                   TRUE ~ present_ratio),
         present_ratio = case_when(Station <= 30 ~ present_ratio,
                                   TRUE ~ as.numeric(NA))) %>%
  distinct(Station, present_ratio, geometry)

detector_presence_by_station_df <- residential_fires_stations_df %>%
  group_by(presence_of_detectors, NAME) %>%
  summarize(count = n()) %>%
  group_by(NAME) %>%
  transmute(
    station = NAME,
    presence_of_detectors,
    count,
    station_prop = count / sum(count)
  )


detector_presence_by_station_crosstab <- detector_presence_by_station_df %>%
  distinct(station, presence_of_detectors, count) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = presence_of_detectors, values_from = count)


structure_fire_count_by_station_df <-
  data.frame(freq(residential_fires_stations_df$Station))

detector_effectiveness_by_station_df <-
  residential_fires_stations_df %>%
  group_by(detector_effectiveness, NAME) %>%
  summarize(count = n()) %>%
  group_by(NAME) %>%
  transmute(
    station = NAME,
    detector_effectiveness,
    count,
    station_prop = count / sum(count)
  )

knitr::kable(structure_fire_freq_tab_df %>% transmute(`Structure Fires` = Freq, Percentage = paste0(round(`X..Total`, 2), "%")) %>% filter(`Structure Fires` > 0))

ggplot(structure_fire_count_by_year_df,
       aes(year, count, fill = incident_type_code)) +
  geom_col() +
  geom_text(aes(label = count),
            size = label_size,
            position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) +
  labs(
    title = "Incident Type by Year",
    subtitle = "Residential Structure Fires\n01/01/2018-12/31/2022",
    caption = "Data Source: ImageTrend  Incident Types: 111, 112  Property Usage Type: 419",
    fill = "Incident Type Code"
  ) +
  xlab(label = "Year") +
  ylab(label = "Residential Structure Fires") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom",
    legend.text = ggplot2::element_text(size = width_scale),
    legend.title = ggplot2::element_text(size = 1.25 * width_scale, face = "bold")
  )

Note on 2018 data: data collection in ImageTrend started during 2018. Documentation errors due to a change in recording methods may contribute to the lower number of residential structure fires in 2018. Further analysis into this anomaly is required.
